Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.12,0:00:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to the program!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.29,0:00:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This month, \Nwe’ll take you to world headquarters
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.99,0:00:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to visit one of the museums.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.73,0:00:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll learn about the many activities\Nthat are organized and directed
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.46,0:00:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,by the Governing Body today.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.40,0:00:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, how can we protect ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.37,0:00:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,from being lured into sin?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.77,0:00:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In this dramatization,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.24,0:00:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,a young brother learns\Nhow to make the right decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.15,0:00:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And how does the organization\Nensure that our brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.98,0:00:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and sisters receive spiritual food?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.29,0:00:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,In this example from Africa,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.29,0:00:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll see how JW Broadcasting® is distributed
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.92,0:00:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,even when Internet connections are slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.43,0:00:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the July 2019 program
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.53,0:00:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of JW Broadcasting!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.72,0:01:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll begin by introducing you\Nto two sisters who live in the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.73,0:01:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Early on in their lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.73,0:01:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,they were exposed to two very different views
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.50,0:01:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of what a family should be like.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.57,0:01:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, they came to realize that,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.14,0:01:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,while life may change, Jehovah doesn’t.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.91,0:01:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my sister Lei Lei.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.18,0:01:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my sister Mimi.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.38,0:01:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,My sister Lei Lei—\NShe is very caring.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.91,0:01:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.32,0:01:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing that I appreciate about Mimi
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.32,0:01:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is that she has a self-sacrificing spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.69,0:01:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We love our family.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.69,0:01:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.93,0:01:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What I love most about my mom\Nis that she has a big heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.10,0:01:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I know that my dad\Nreally, truly loves his family.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.17,0:02:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Our sister, Sophie, always takes care of you,\Nmaking sure you are OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.07,0:02:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Our family is something\Nthat we never want to replace.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.38,0:02:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,To us, it’s a forever family.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.48,0:02:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But it wasn’t always like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.39,0:02:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We haven’t always been sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.32,0:02:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,At a young age,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.36,0:02:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I was already in a foster home,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.10,0:02:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and then Mimi became my foster sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.87,0:02:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We were not treated as part of their family.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.90,0:02:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We never knew what love felt like.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.14,0:02:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,There wasn’t a bedroom for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.51,0:02:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Me and Lei Lei would share a couch.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.71,0:02:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Our foster families would leave us
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.71,0:02:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,by ourselves at home,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.32,0:02:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and me and Lei Lei had to take care of ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.42,0:02:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we were very close together
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.55,0:02:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,because we would talk to each other\Nand just help each other out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.19,0:02:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,When we would go to school,\Nwe didn’t have school supplies,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.53,0:03:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,so I would steal stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.70,0:03:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And we didn’t have school uniforms;
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.93,0:03:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we had clothing that was dirty.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.60,0:03:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like in some way\Nthat with all these experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.44,0:03:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,it kind of made me feel like I didn’t care.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.91,0:03:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t like authority figures\Nand didn’t really trust them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.61,0:03:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I was lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.35,0:03:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I was confused.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.15,0:03:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I just did whatever I possibly could
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.69,0:03:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to protect myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.75,0:03:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We have experienced things\Nthat no child should go through.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.29,0:03:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We found out there was a family\Nwho wanted to adopt us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.00,0:03:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I was 12 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.10,0:03:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was nine years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.80,0:03:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing that was tough for me was conversing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.34,0:03:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t know any English,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.78,0:03:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was hard for my parents to know how I felt
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.65,0:03:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because I had a hard time\Nexpressing if I was sad or scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.15,0:03:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a difficult time trusting.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.45,0:03:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But they showed us love,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.59,0:04:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and they hugged us\Nand just made us feel at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.30,0:04:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,As I got to know them better and I got to see
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.66,0:04:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that they truly loved me
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.87,0:04:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and that they truly treated me like their daughter,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.14,0:04:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it helped me to develop love and trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.71,0:04:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The first time I saw\Nmy mom and dad praying at the dinner meal,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.08,0:04:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it was very new to me because I never knew
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.58,0:04:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that there was a God.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.65,0:04:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I had some past experience with religion,\Nand I didn’t like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.52,0:04:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I first saw my mom and dad praying,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.32,0:04:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I was uncomfortable with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.93,0:04:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They had to figure out a way
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.96,0:04:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to introduce their best Friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.70,0:04:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.63,0:04:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They took us to this place\Ncalled the Kingdom Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.67,0:04:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The first thing we felt was warmth and love.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.61,0:04:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All these friends were coming up
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.61,0:04:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and saying hi to us and giving us hugs
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.68,0:04:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,—just super loving toward us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.58,0:05:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad would give us a notepad,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.02,0:05:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and he would tell us,\N“Draw anything that you understand.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.72,0:05:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And so those were our notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.22,0:05:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We would just draw pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.39,0:05:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They would pray with us,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.16,0:05:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,teaching us how to pray specifically
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.36,0:05:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and to see how Jehovah\Ncould answer our prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.20,0:05:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We would eat breakfast\Nevery day together and do the daily text;
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.24,0:05:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,we would reenact Bible stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.81,0:05:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And we prepared for meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.05,0:05:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The simplified Watchtower came out,\Nand it really helped us so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.52,0:05:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I was able to really learn\Nmore about Jehovah and understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.12,0:05:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And that helped me to give\Nmore comments and draw closer to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.49,0:05:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,A big change for me
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.53,0:05:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,was during the 2014 international convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.73,0:05:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Just seeing the love and the unity
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.83,0:05:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,between brothers and sisters touched my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.37,0:05:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That also helped me
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.51,0:05:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to progress toward making\Nthe decision of getting baptized.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.51,0:06:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Going out in service more—\NI think it really helped me
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.68,0:06:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to draw closer to Jehovah\Nand make the Kingdom feel real to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.48,0:06:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that’s why I wanted to get baptized.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.29,0:06:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,After I graduated from high school,\NI started to pioneer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.76,0:06:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s one way to show my love for Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.30,0:06:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to just take care of myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.20,0:06:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but I learned to take care of others\Nand to think of others first.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.70,0:06:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,For us young ones, we should appreciate
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.21,0:06:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,every moment that we have with our parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.51,0:06:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Your parents are the best friends\Nthat you could ever have.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.58,0:06:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Going out in service wasn’t easy for me at first
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.71,0:06:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,because I’m actually a very shy person,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.65,0:06:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but I decided to rely on Jehovah\Nand started pioneering.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.12,0:06:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And just recently,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.22,0:06:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I started commuting to Bethel one day a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.73,0:06:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The important quality\Nthat Jehovah has taught me is love
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.13,0:07:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt that love from my family,\Nfrom Jehovah, and from my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.14,0:07:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned that it’s OK to love people,\Nand that’s what you are supposed to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.64,0:07:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You love people and take care of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.64,0:07:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And I feel like my life\Nis more satisfying and meaningful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.98,0:07:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,When I meditate and think\Nabout what Jehovah has done for me and Lei Lei,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.75,0:07:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t have to be afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.76,0:07:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is my “secure refuge,”\Nbecause life may change,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.36,0:07:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jehovah does not change.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.73,0:07:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The love and unity of the brothers\Nstood out to Lei Lei and Mimi
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.47,0:07:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and helped them draw closer to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.84,0:07:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,For a Bible student to progress to baptism,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.84,0:07:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,he or she would need to develop\Nthose very qualities,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.04,0:07:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,which Lei Lei and Mimi did.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.68,0:07:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are\Nmany additional aspects of our personality
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.75,0:07:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that we as Christians need to maintain.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.59,0:07:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the most underrated qualities
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.59,0:07:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in today’s world is modesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.39,0:07:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, the world encourages
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.46,0:08:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the exact opposite of modesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.06,0:08:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The world says that you are\Nthe most important person;
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.00,0:08:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you should promote yourself;\Nyou have no limits;
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.21,0:08:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you have the right to be anything you want to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.58,0:08:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,As we’ll see, the world’s thinking\Nis completely backward
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.85,0:08:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,—and for several reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.02,0:08:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, modesty is a quality
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.89,0:08:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that stems from everything that is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.46,0:08:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Our theme scripture\Nfor this discussion is Micah 6:8:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.20,0:08:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“He has told you . . . what is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.90,0:08:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“And what is Jehovah requiring of you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.60,0:08:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“Only to exercise justice, to cherish loyalty,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.31,0:08:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and to walk in modesty with your God!”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.61,0:08:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice that modesty is one
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.61,0:08:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of the key aspects of “what is good.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.78,0:08:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,To help us understand why,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.05,0:08:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s discuss three questions:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.15,0:08:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What is modesty?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.59,0:09:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we want to have this quality?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.49,0:09:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we cultivate it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.73,0:09:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,First, what is modesty?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.80,0:09:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Basically, it’s an awareness of our limitations.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.94,0:09:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we often link modesty
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.27,0:09:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,with appropriate dress and grooming,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.51,0:09:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,but much more is involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.24,0:09:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we know?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.25,0:09:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider what we read at Proverbs 11:2:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.12,0:09:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“When presumptuousness comes,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.92,0:09:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“dishonor will follow,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.92,0:09:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but wisdom is with the modest ones.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.72,0:09:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice that modesty is contrasted
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.09,0:09:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,with a negative quality—presumptuousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.56,0:09:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A presumptuous person\Nruns ahead without the authority to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.37,0:09:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He or she ignores\Nproper boundaries and limitations.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.74,0:09:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That kind of attitude\Noften leads to foolish mistakes
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.01,0:09:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and a bad reputation with fellow humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.71,0:10:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And above all,\Nit can cause a person to lose God’s favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.32,0:10:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, we might think of King Saul.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.65,0:10:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Although he started out as a modest young man,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.76,0:10:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,in time he became presumptuous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.66,0:10:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He even went so far as to offer up
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.83,0:10:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,a burnt sacrifice\Neven though he was not authorized to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.50,0:10:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.50,0:10:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Saul lost Jehovah’s favor
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.24,0:10:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and eventually the kingship.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.41,0:10:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,In Saul’s case, presumptuousness definitely
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.01,0:10:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,led to dishonor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.01,0:10:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.02,0:10:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,a wise and modest person
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.02,0:10:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,recognizes his limitations and works within them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.42,0:10:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is modesty the course of wisdom?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.36,0:10:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This brings us to our second main point,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.03,0:10:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we want to have this quality?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.07,0:10:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The foremost reason
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.07,0:10:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is that modesty is essential
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.80,0:10:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to pleasing our heavenly Father, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.67,0:10:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Although we don’t speak\Nof Jehovah as being modest,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.81,0:11:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,even he works within certain limitations
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.58,0:11:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that he’s imposed on himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.98,0:11:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He teaches us by example\Nhow to demonstrate this quality,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.42,0:11:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,even though it’s not one that he needs to display.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.62,0:11:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Why can we say that Jehovah\Nimposes limitations on himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.63,0:11:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider just one example:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.10,0:11:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He’ll never violate\Nthe gift of free will that he’s granted us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.90,0:11:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will never force us to serve him
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.14,0:11:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,—even though, of course,\Nhe has the power to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.04,0:11:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren’t we grateful that he allows us to serve him
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.68,0:11:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because we choose to out of love
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.98,0:11:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and not because we are forced to?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.69,0:11:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah teaches us\Nto display modesty in other ways as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.56,0:11:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, we might think\Nof how he listened patiently
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.79,0:11:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,as Abraham voiced his concerns\Nabout Jehovah’s purpose
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.63,0:11:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to destroy Sodom and Gomorrah
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.50,0:12:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,or how Jehovah invited\Nthe angels to suggest ways to fool Ahab
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.44,0:12:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and then authorized\None of their suggestions to be carried out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.54,0:12:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the lesson for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.01,0:12:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If Jehovah, who doesn’t need\Ninput or help from anyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.55,0:12:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,patiently listens and delegates,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.12,0:12:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,how much more should we do so
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.45,0:12:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,—especially since\Nwe’re all so imperfect and limited!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.36,0:12:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you a family head\Nor an elder in the congregation,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.33,0:12:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,or do you have\Nanother responsible position in the organization?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.50,0:12:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, you can imitate Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.54,0:12:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,by not micromanaging others.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.47,0:12:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Be willing to delegate tasks to them
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.67,0:12:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and listen to their suggestions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.91,0:12:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Imitate Jehovah’s example of dignifying others
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.51,0:12:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and wanting to help them succeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.62,0:12:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides pleasing Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.82,0:12:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we have other good reasons to be modest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.96,0:12:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Modesty helps us to be joyful.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.03,0:12:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,How so?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.73,0:13:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,By going hand in hand\Nwith a related quality—gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.43,0:13:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,A faithful brother who worked\Nin the Writing Department
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.64,0:13:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for some 50 years was fond of saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.64,0:13:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“Only a grateful person can be happy.”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.48,0:13:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If we’re modestly aware of our limitations,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.48,0:13:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll be grateful and happy
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.91,0:13:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,for the help that we receive from others.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.78,0:13:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,For example,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.52,0:13:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,think of the leper who returned
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.52,0:13:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to thank Jesus for healing him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.99,0:13:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This man realized his limitations.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.69,0:13:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He was very thankful that Jesus\Nhad done something for him
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.73,0:13:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that he could never have done on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.83,0:13:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Another reason to cultivate modesty
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.60,0:13:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is that it promotes good relationships with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.47,0:13:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s face it:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.48,0:13:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,People aren’t usually drawn to those who think,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.41,0:13:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,‘If I want something done right,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.65,0:13:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to do it myself.’
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.05,0:13:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But they usually appreciate it when they’re shown
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.35,0:14:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have confidence in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.89,0:14:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This, in turn, draws them to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.09,0:14:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Another way that modesty\Npromotes good relationships
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.60,0:14:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is that it helps us\Nto avoid comparing ourselves to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.14,0:14:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Comparing ourselves to others
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.84,0:14:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is always a dangerous road to navigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.41,0:14:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Just think, for example, of Jesus’ apostles
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.78,0:14:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,who argued many times\Nover who was the greatest
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.45,0:14:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,or of Joseph’s brothers\Nand the terrible things they did
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.75,0:14:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,because of being jealous of Joseph.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.89,0:14:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,A modest person doesn’t obsess
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.26,0:14:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,over his perceived rank in comparison with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.40,0:14:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In this regard,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.13,0:14:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we can remember the good example of Moses.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.80,0:14:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How did he react when Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.80,0:14:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,enabled some of his fellow Israelites
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.14,0:14:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to begin acting as prophets alongside him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.81,0:14:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Moses rejoiced,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.88,0:14:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,saying that he wished all\Nof Jehovah’s people were prophets.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.48,0:15:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Moses didn’t feel that he was\Nthe only one who should have such a privilege.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.92,0:15:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, modesty promotes\Ngood relationships with others
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.63,0:15:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,because it prevents us\Nfrom bragging about our accomplishments
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.56,0:15:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,or drawing undue attention to ourselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.57,0:15:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,which could stir up resentment in others.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.60,0:15:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So now we know what modesty is\Nand why we want to have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.44,0:15:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This brings us to our third main point,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.08,0:15:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we cultivate this beautiful quality?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.58,0:15:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing we can do
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.25,0:15:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is to read and meditate on Bible examples
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.32,0:15:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,—both good and bad—\Nsuch as those we just discussed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.79,0:15:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Other Bible examples include Daniel,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.53,0:15:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,who modestly didn’t take credit
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.53,0:15:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,for the interpretation\Nof King Nebuchadnezzar’s dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.03,0:15:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The lesson for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.17,0:15:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If we’re privileged to have a teaching assignment
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.17,0:15:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,or we enjoy a measure of success in the ministry,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.54,0:16:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to give all the glory to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.04,0:16:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We should modestly recognize
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.21,0:16:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that we couldn’t do these things without his help.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.22,0:16:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We can also study the example of Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.05,0:16:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,who didn’t even think of trying to grasp
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.46,0:16:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,for more authority than Jehovah had granted him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.79,0:16:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Philippians 2:6 tells us:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.00,0:16:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“He . . . gave no consideration to a seizure,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.17,0:16:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,namely, that he should be equal to God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.47,0:16:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider how Jesus responded
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.47,0:16:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,when his disciples James\Nand John approached him
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.11,0:16:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,with their mother\Nand asked for a privilege
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.01,0:16:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that was beyond his authority to grant them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.75,0:16:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus modestly acknowledged
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.85,0:16:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that only Jehovah could decide
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.55,0:16:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,who would sit at his right\Nand left hand in the Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.19,0:16:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus respected his limitations.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.46,0:16:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What are some other ways\Nwe can cultivate modesty?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.00,0:16:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,One is to apply the Bible’s counsel
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.47,0:17:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,found at 1 Corinthians 4:6:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.14,0:17:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not go beyond the things that are written.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.74,0:17:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This refers primarily\Nto ‘the things written’ in God’s Word.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.48,0:17:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,By extension, the principle\Nalso applies to the Scriptural direction
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.25,0:17:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that we receive from our publications.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.09,0:17:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,When asked for advice,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.09,0:17:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we would never want to impose our own opinion
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.29,0:17:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,or simply give an answer off the top of our head.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.73,0:17:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, we want to direct attention
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.43,0:17:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to the counsel found in the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.57,0:17:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and Bible-based publications.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.77,0:17:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Another way we can cultivate modesty
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.60,0:17:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is by asking for frank comments
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.84,0:17:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,from a trusted friend
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.84,0:17:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,as to whether or not\Nwe have a reputation for being modest.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.31,0:17:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In this regard, we remember the Bible principle:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.52,0:17:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“As iron sharpens iron,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.95,0:17:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,so one man sharpens his friend.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.56,0:17:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If someone is willing to offer
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.56,0:17:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,kind observations about how we can improve,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.36,0:18:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we wouldn’t want to bristle at the comments.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.73,0:18:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Granted, it may sting our pride\Nto hear such honest feedback,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.20,0:18:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,but don’t we all need\Nto hear these things from time to time?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.37,0:18:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,As imperfect humans,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.38,0:18:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,each one of us has blind spots, as it were.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.95,0:18:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s hard to see ourselves the way others see us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.88,0:18:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, we can work\Nto improve our Christian personality
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.72,0:18:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,—but only if we know\Nthe areas that could use some improvement.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.36,0:18:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We can’t change what we don’t see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.63,0:18:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,A word of caution:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.63,0:18:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to beware of false modesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.53,0:18:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember that it’s not\Nabout simply appearing modest
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.27,0:18:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,but actually being modest at heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.84,0:18:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,To help us examine ourselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.11,0:18:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,we might meditate on questions like these:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.71,0:18:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,When I receive advice or counsel,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.42,0:18:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,how do I really feel about it at heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.82,0:19:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Does my internal reaction\Ndepend on whether the person giving it
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.92,0:19:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,has less or more experience\Nor authority than I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.36,0:19:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I willing to accept valid suggestions\Nregardless of who offers them?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.53,0:19:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,A final way we can develop true modesty
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.10,0:19:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is to ask Jehovah to help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.21,0:19:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We know what James 1:17 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.78,0:19:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“Every good gift and every perfect present is from above,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.78,0:19:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,coming down from the Father of the celestial lights.”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.65,0:19:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Since modesty is one of Jehovah’s good gifts to us,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.39,0:19:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we can be sure that if we pray to Jehovah and ask him
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.76,0:19:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to help us cultivate this quality,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.30,0:19:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,he’ll answer our sincere prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.90,0:19:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In review, what is modesty?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.94,0:19:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a proper recognition of our limitations.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.77,0:19:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we want to have this quality?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.54,0:19:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it pleases Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.88,0:20:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,it promotes good relationships with others,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.08,0:20:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and it adds to our joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.02,0:20:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we cultivate modesty?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.66,0:20:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many ways:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.66,0:20:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We can meditate on Bible examples,\Nboth good and bad,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.46,0:20:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and then apply the lessons in our own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.40,0:20:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We should apply the counsel\Nto ‘not go beyond the things written.’
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.57,0:20:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We can ask others for honest feedback
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.14,0:20:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,on how we’re doing in showing this quality.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.71,0:20:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And above all, we can pray to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.84,0:20:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask him to help us develop it more fully.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.85,0:20:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,When we think of all the positive ways
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.38,0:20:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that modesty benefits ourselves and others,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.29,0:20:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn’t you agree that it truly is a quality
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.02,0:20:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that comes from “what is good”?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.93,0:20:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Modesty can also protect us\Nfrom Satan’s schemes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.93,0:20:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,In this dramatization,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.03,0:20:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,a brother’s modesty\Nhelped him to make the right decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.98,0:21:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom has been working hard lately,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.65,0:21:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but I wish she worked harder for Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.69,0:21:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I try to help out where I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.63,0:21:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, by the way, I’m Jin.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.24,0:21:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day starts the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.84,0:21:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I grab a drink of water;
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.08,0:21:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I say hi to Jun (he’s in my congregation);
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.02,0:21:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and then there’s Mee-Kyong.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.52,0:21:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.\NHere we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.52,0:21:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I say hello,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.56,0:21:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,she says something clever,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.23,0:21:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and I try to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.73,0:21:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.73,0:22:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s having trouble\Nin math and needs my help.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.31,0:22:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t want to be rude,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.58,0:22:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,but
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.11,0:22:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,if I help her with her homework,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.45,0:22:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,how far could the relationship develop?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.62,0:22:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you say no to a girl like her?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.29,0:22:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Why can’t I get her out of my head?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.01,0:23:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Things are always better
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.01,0:23:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,when Uncle and Auntie are around.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.65,0:23:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Even Mom makes sure\Nshe’s home for “dinner and broadcast” night.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.96,0:23:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Uncle wants to work together\Nin service this weekend;
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.97,0:23:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe that will help clear my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.36,0:24:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah must be disappointed in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.04,0:24:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t take it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.64,0:24:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It was difficult,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.64,0:24:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but I told Uncle everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.81,0:24:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt guilty that I knew I shouldn’t,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.72,0:24:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but I liked the attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.82,0:24:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We read Genesis 39:7-12.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.93,0:24:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew the account about Potiphar’s wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.79,0:24:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,but he mentioned something\NI hadn’t thought of before.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.73,0:24:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He told Potiphar’s wife:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.00,0:24:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“How could I commit this great badness
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.07,0:24:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and actually sin against God?”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.11,0:24:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But why did Joseph have to flee?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.12,0:25:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph fought her every day,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.19,0:25:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,but she wasn’t going to give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.23,0:25:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In her mind,\Nit wasn’t a question of if but when.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.23,0:25:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,There came a point when he had to flee.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.47,0:25:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I explained why I was ending the relationship,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.68,0:25:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but she would not give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.96,0:25:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You know the last thing she said to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.26,0:25:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That I was a coward.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.49,0:25:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But she’s wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.40,0:25:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re never a coward if you run to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.80,0:25:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Our young brother \Nsaw that dating an unbeliever
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.94,0:25:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,would put him in harm’s way.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.44,0:26:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He was reminded that getting involved
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.74,0:26:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,with someone\Nwho doesn’t share Jehovah’s values
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.65,0:26:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,could eventually lead to sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.25,0:26:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Having modesty protected him\Nfrom such dire consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.65,0:26:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,By his decision,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.66,0:26:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,we could see our young brother’s faith in action.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.36,0:26:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Faith in Action\Nis also the name of one of the museums
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.36,0:26:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,at our world headquarters in Warwick, New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.63,0:26:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you had an opportunity to visit?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.60,0:26:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If not, we’d like to take you there right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.34,0:26:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And even if you have visited,\Nyou’ll enjoy these reminders.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.77,0:27:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to the World Headquarters
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.98,0:27:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jehovah’s Witnesses at Warwick, New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.35,0:27:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,As Jehovah’s people,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.38,0:27:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,we are multicultural and multilingual.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.62,0:27:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And as the artwork here emphasizes, our focus
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.65,0:27:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is on our commission to ‘preach the good news
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.69,0:27:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to people of all nations.’
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.69,0:27:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what are we doing today as an organization?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.06,0:27:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,How did we get here?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.07,0:27:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And what’s our main tool for this great work?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.34,0:27:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We invite you to come tour our museums
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.47,0:27:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.74,0:27:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We have three museums here at Warwick,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.18,0:27:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,all funded by voluntary donations.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.31,0:27:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Each of them is alive with stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.58,0:27:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Upstairs on the second floor
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.92,0:27:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is the museum Faith in Action.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.52,0:27:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There we’ll see the very latest
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.03,0:28:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,on what’s being done by Jehovah’s organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.40,0:28:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Also on the second floor is the museum
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.43,0:28:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,A People for Jehovah’s Name.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.54,0:28:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes us on an exciting journey back in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.57,0:28:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And downstairs
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.58,0:28:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,we have the Bible Museum.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.08,0:28:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There we’ll get to see up close
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.68,0:28:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,a spiritual treasure chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.45,0:28:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,When you tour the museums,\Nyou’ll notice that they
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.02,0:28:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,were designed to be, not passive, but interactive
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.59,0:28:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you can put yourself in the experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.53,0:28:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So with that preview,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.73,0:28:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s take the tour.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.94,0:28:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the launching point\Nto the Faith in Action Museum.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.94,0:28:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Note that important, descriptive word: “action.”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.25,0:28:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What activities, or actions,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.72,0:28:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,are being organized and directed
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.82,0:28:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,by the Governing Body today?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.05,0:29:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This display acquaints you right away
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.42,0:29:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,with the work of the Governing Body committees.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.12,0:29:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Each committee has specific responsibilities,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.83,0:29:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,but as you take the tour,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.43,0:29:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,notice how the committees work together
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.43,0:29:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to accomplish their goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.60,0:29:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The Faith in Action Museum
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.24,0:29:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is divided into four galleries:
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.61,0:29:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“Show Love,”
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.11,0:29:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“Meet Together,”
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.81,0:29:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“Take In Spiritual Food,”
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.45,0:29:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and “Make Disciples.”
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.32,0:29:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,As you walk through the galleries,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.98,0:29:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,notice how each of them\Nis connected by a JW-blue ribbon.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.62,0:29:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you get lost,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.62,0:29:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,just follow the blue ribbon.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.93,0:29:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the “Show Love” Gallery.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.10,0:29:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you’ll learn how the Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.47,0:29:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,helps God’s people\Nto ‘have love among themselves,’
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.97,0:29:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,as Jesus commanded at John 13:35.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.11,0:29:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,For example,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.34,0:29:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,how do the brothers at headquarters respond
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.35,0:30:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to needs that arise when a disaster strikes?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.92,0:30:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,When things like natural disasters,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.69,0:30:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,terrorist attacks, or civil unrest occur,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.69,0:30:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the Coordinators’ Committee directs relief efforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.33,0:30:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They, in turn, communicate\Nwith the Branch Committee
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.56,0:30:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that oversees the affected area.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.90,0:30:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually, within 48 hours,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.90,0:30:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,a report of what’s occurred
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.34,0:30:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and what’s being done to help our brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.71,0:30:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is compiled and sent to headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.84,0:30:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That report may be\Nthe basis for informing the brotherhood
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.55,0:30:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,through an article on jw.org®.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.52,0:30:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s another way that love\Nis shown to Jehovah’s people
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.92,0:30:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,—schools.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.39,0:30:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Such schools as the School for Congregation Elders
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.83,0:30:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and the School for Circuit Overseers and Their Wives.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.56,0:30:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,These have been very effective in training brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.77,0:30:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to shepherd the congregations lovingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.34,0:30:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The Teaching Committee\Nis responsible for the curriculum,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.51,0:31:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,while the Service Committee\Narranges for the selection of the students.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.05,0:31:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the “Meet Together” Gallery.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.72,0:31:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you’ll learn how\Nthe Governing Body is helping God’s people
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.62,0:31:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to meet together “to incite
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.79,0:31:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to love and fine works,” as directed
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.29,0:31:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,at Hebrews 10:24, 25.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.63,0:31:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,How is the headquarters staff\Nat Warwick filling that need?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.10,0:31:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we keep growing,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.54,0:31:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s an ongoing need
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.47,0:31:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to build new Kingdom Halls\Nand to renovate existing ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.41,0:31:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The Publishing Committee of the Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.14,0:31:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,directs where Kingdom Halls will be built
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.08,0:31:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and makes funds available to the branches.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.22,0:31:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The Publishing Committee
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.25,0:31:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,works closely with the branch office,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.79,0:31:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and its Local Design/Construction Department
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.29,0:31:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,carries out the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.29,0:31:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But where do these hardworking
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.29,0:31:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,brothers and sisters come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.30,0:31:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The Personnel Committee
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.30,0:31:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,appoints all construction servants
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.30,0:32:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,for assignments in their home country
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.50,0:32:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,or in a foreign land.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.04,0:32:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you worked on a theocratic building project?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.44,0:32:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Take our survey, and let us know.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.35,0:32:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Some Kingdom Halls are located in areas
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.62,0:32:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,where there is little or no electricity,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.58,0:32:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but that doesn’t stop us from meeting together.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.12,0:32:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The Publishing Committee
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.42,0:32:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,has arranged for a custom-built, portable sound system
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.93,0:32:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to be used in these areas.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.53,0:32:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The unity player has a battery
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.17,0:32:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that can be recharged by its solar panel
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.04,0:32:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,or with a built-in hand crank.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.80,0:32:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a wonderful provision
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.27,0:32:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that helps our brothers and sisters benefit more
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.18,0:32:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,from their congregation meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.78,0:32:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the “Take In Spiritual Food” Gallery.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.15,0:32:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you guess what design we used?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.12,0:32:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s right, a dining table.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.16,0:32:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you’ll learn how the Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.46,0:32:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,fulfills the Scriptural commission
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.66,0:33:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,at Luke 12:42
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.90,0:33:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to feed God’s people spiritually.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.20,0:33:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,To accomplish this,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.23,0:33:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,millions of Bibles, books,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.07,0:33:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and other publications
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.91,0:33:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,need to be prepared, translated, and printed.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.68,0:33:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.68,0:33:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,a regular flow of material is released online.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.42,0:33:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Translators around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.42,0:33:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,keep in close contact with Translation Services
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.89,0:33:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,—a headquarters department
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.89,0:33:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s supervised by the Writing Committee.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.86,0:33:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a favorite publication?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.93,0:33:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Much more is involved than just the writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.57,0:33:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The section “From Start to Finish”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.44,0:33:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,outlines 11 steps
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.00,0:33:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that are taken to produce the final product.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.21,0:33:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What about our online spiritual food?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.28,0:33:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Each month, we look forward
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.05,0:33:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to a new JW Broadcasting® program.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.18,0:33:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the Teaching Committee approves a video idea,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.02,0:34:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Audio/Video Services researches the subject
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.56,0:34:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and prepares a script for final approval.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.33,0:34:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Approved scripts and storyboards
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.73,0:34:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,are assigned\Nto video production teams around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.57,0:34:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This gives our videos an international flavor.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.77,0:34:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we’ve come\Nto our final gallery, “Make Disciples.”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.61,0:34:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you’ll learn how\Nthe Governing Body is helping us
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.11,0:34:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to fulfill the Scriptural commission
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.38,0:34:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,at Matthew 28:19
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.79,0:34:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to “make disciples of people
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.82,0:34:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of all [the] nations, baptizing them.”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.72,0:34:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The command to preach can be daunting,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.43,0:34:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,especially in certain lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.80,0:34:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So how are we meeting that challenge?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.73,0:34:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The Service Committee oversees
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.40,0:34:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the preaching work worldwide.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.64,0:34:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They help all to have a share according to their ability
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.27,0:34:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,—some as congregation publishers,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.68,0:34:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,others as full-time evangelizers.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.28,0:35:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, special preaching campaigns
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.48,0:35:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and public witnessing\Nhave resulted in many new Bible studies.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.95,0:35:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,At times, though,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.96,0:35:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,our religious freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.99,0:35:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is opposed by secular authorities.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.16,0:35:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Coordinators’ Committee supervises
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.27,0:35:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the World Headquarters Legal Department.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.10,0:35:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Many courts have handed down favorable decisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.87,0:35:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, we must continue
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.47,0:35:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to defend our right to preach the good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.25,0:35:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Our online tools are also\Na huge help in making disciples.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.12,0:35:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This counter shows the average rate
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.65,0:35:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,at which people worldwide
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.69,0:35:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,are logging on to jw.org.®
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.36,0:35:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Each day, some 250 Bible studies
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.76,0:35:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,are requested online.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.00,0:35:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Schools also help us to make disciples.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.87,0:35:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We have the Pioneer Service School,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.64,0:35:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the School for Kingdom Evangelizers,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.87,0:36:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and Gilead School.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.81,0:36:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you attended one of these schools?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.65,0:36:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us know.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.42,0:36:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as we come to the end of our tour,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.42,0:36:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,we hope you enjoyed some highlights
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.59,0:36:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,from this Faith in Action Museum.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.76,0:36:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What we’ve seen here reminds us
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.26,0:36:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that now and always
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.93,0:36:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s people are a people of faith
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.90,0:36:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,—faith in action!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.40,0:36:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,As Brother Sanderson highlighted,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.84,0:36:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the organization’s actions speak volumes
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.81,0:36:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,of the faith of Jehovah’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.41,0:36:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And we wanted to share\None more example of faith in action.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.32,0:36:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In Africa, a new provision has made it easier
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.15,0:36:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,for our brothers and sisters\Nto access spiritual food.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.76,0:36:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of the electronic information
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.76,0:36:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that had been translated and provided
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.63,0:37:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,for the brothers in sub-Saharan Africa
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.47,0:37:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,was essentially unavailable to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.61,0:37:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many areas in Mozambique
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.97,0:37:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that do not have Internet access,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.54,0:37:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and in some parts
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.78,0:37:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no cell phone coverage.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.88,0:37:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So we started investigating
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.88,0:37:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,what it would take to have a 24-hour-a-day,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.85,0:37:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,7-day-a-week satellite channel
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.22,0:37:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,dedicated to JW Broadcasting®.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.69,0:37:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,When the announcement was made to our congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.69,0:37:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,about the JW satellite channel,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.69,0:37:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,our brothers and sisters\Nwere very happy about the announcement.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.13,0:37:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Our organization has a lot of experience
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.97,0:37:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,distributing video via the Internet,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.14,0:37:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but to distribute it on the satellite was entirely new,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.64,0:37:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so we had to do a lot of research.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.68,0:37:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t have our own satellite up in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.38,0:37:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We rent a channel on a satellite\Nthat covers sub-Saharan Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.05,0:37:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What is required from the brothers is
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.05,0:37:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to have a satellite dish and a decoder.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.22,0:37:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This will allow them\Nto view the channel with no additional cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.10,0:38:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers that are invited
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.77,0:38:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to come here are trained.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.40,0:38:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,First, how to set up the dish.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.84,0:38:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, how to set up the decoder
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.84,0:38:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and learn how to adjust the dish properly
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.88,0:38:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so that it works well.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.88,0:38:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we teach them how to record the programs
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.08,0:38:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,with the goal that they can watch it\Nwith the brothers and sisters in the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.06,0:38:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Our satellite channel is set up to transmit
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.12,0:38:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,one video track and 16 audio tracks.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.19,0:38:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This gives us the ability to broadcast our videos
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.10,0:38:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in 16 languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.27,0:38:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We consulted\Nwith the Translation Services Department,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.04,0:38:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and so these are the 16 languages
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.04,0:38:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that give us the greatest audience\Nof our brothers in Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.58,0:38:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We wrote new software that takes\Nany new video that comes to JW Broadcasting®
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.78,0:38:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and mixes the 16 languages\Nof video together into a single video file
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.05,0:38:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and delivers that to our satellite provider.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.05,0:39:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.05,0:39:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,lovingly approved\Nfor the rental cost of the satellite channel
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.76,0:39:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to be covered\Nfrom contributions to the worldwide work.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.16,0:39:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So there’s no expense to the brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.93,0:39:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in Africa to receive the program.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.00,0:39:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We broadcast over
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.24,0:39:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,a single satellite channel for most of our needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.17,0:39:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But occasionally, we use a second channel
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.74,0:39:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,when we broadcast live events, like conventions
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.01,0:39:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,or branch visits.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.78,0:39:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,When the representative\Nfrom world headquarters gives his talk
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.32,0:39:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,from Bethel, it is transmitted to us
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.32,0:39:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,live through the satellite.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.75,0:39:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This makes us feel like we
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.25,0:39:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,are right there at Bethel.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.86,0:39:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We are very happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.96,0:39:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The most recent live event
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.29,0:39:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that we broadcasted originated in France.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.93,0:39:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the release of the revised edition\Nof the New World Translation,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.43,0:39:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,so this was very exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.47,0:39:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And brothers and sisters\Nthat attended conventions
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.87,0:39:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in ten different branch territories in Africa
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.71,0:39:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,were able to tie in\Nto this broadcast that originated in France,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.84,0:39:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,using the satellite.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.35,0:40:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,In our branch territory,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.35,0:40:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,we are arranging\Nfor all new or remodeled Kingdom Halls
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.39,0:40:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to have satellite equipment\Nas part of the standard audio/video package.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.76,0:40:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We were very happy
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.19,0:40:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,when we received the satellite dish
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.99,0:40:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,because we could see that now
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.73,0:40:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,we are really close \Nto the brothers on the Governing Body.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.07,0:40:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The satellite channel is excellent!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.34,0:40:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This provision touches our hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.74,0:40:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The deaf all over the country\Nbenefited from the special talk
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.54,0:40:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,as it was interpreted\Ninto Malawian Sign Language,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.38,0:40:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,showing that Jehovah truly loves deaf people.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.38,0:40:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And this helps us\Nto strengthen our relationship with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.33,0:40:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We hope and pray\Nthat access to the JW satellite feed
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.23,0:40:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes available\Nto as many of our brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.37,0:41:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,as possible in sub-Saharan Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.43,0:41:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,As we could see,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.43,0:41:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the organization prioritizes\Nthe needs of Jehovah’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.54,0:41:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And as it does, it finds a modest solution
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.21,0:41:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that can best serve the needs\Nof as many people as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.38,0:41:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,As we discussed earlier in the program,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.18,0:41:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,modesty is equally important on an individual level.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.05,0:41:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are times when we have to ask ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.29,0:41:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,if we’re confusing modesty
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.49,0:41:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,with our own imperfect view of ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.13,0:41:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Meet Juan Cayul from Chile.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.69,0:41:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s of the Mapuche tribe
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.80,0:41:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,—a tribe which has faced  \Ndiscrimination over the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.33,0:42:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the discrimination,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.67,0:42:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,some may be reluctant to use their language,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.77,0:42:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Mapudungún, in public.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.24,0:42:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This became a challenge for Juan,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.74,0:42:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,since he wanted to give\Nhis best in the ministry for Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.58,0:42:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Mapudungún means ‘the speech of my land.’
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.95,0:42:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a beautiful and expressive language,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.16,0:42:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and it’s the language of my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.96,0:42:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was 12 years old, I went to live
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.73,0:42:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,with my grandfather and my uncle’s family
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.73,0:42:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so that I could study at a nearby school.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.00,0:42:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,My cousins spoke Mapudungún a lot,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.47,0:42:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,which made me really happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.37,0:42:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,When I saw that some of my classmates\Ndidn’t understand their schoolwork,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.68,0:42:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,especially in math class,\NI would try to help them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.85,0:42:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s when I started to think about becoming
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.58,0:42:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,a math teacher so that I could really help others.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.46,0:42:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But the head teacher told me\Nthat because I was speaking
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.96,0:43:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Mapudungún and because\NI was helping my classmates,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.13,0:43:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,she was going to lower my grades.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.90,0:43:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,When my father saw my grades, he was furious.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.74,0:43:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He accused me of being lazy and not studying.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.07,0:43:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He withdrew me from school,\Nand I went back home to Tromén.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.21,0:43:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,My dream of becoming a teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.25,0:43:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,was shattered.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.25,0:43:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Because my dad had suffered so much\Nas a victim of discrimination,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.36,0:43:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,he told us that we\Nwere not to speak Mapudungún.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.43,0:43:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,When I think about everything that happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.90,0:43:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it makes me very sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.07,0:43:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Years later, I met Sylvia
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.24,0:43:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,who was Mapuche like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.84,0:43:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,She proved to be a sensitive and loving person.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.45,0:43:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We spoke Mapudungún together,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.12,0:43:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and that helped to relieve the bitterness
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.42,0:43:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt in my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.26,0:44:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Some time later, I learned about someone else
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.96,0:44:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,who made me feel loved and valued—Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.49,0:44:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That changed my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.33,0:44:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All my pain disappeared
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.80,0:44:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,once I got to know Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.64,0:44:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife and I studied the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.34,0:44:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,with the Witnesses in Spanish.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.61,0:44:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And so when I started to preach and teach,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.68,0:44:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I used Spanish too.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.25,0:44:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, I was out in service,\Nand as we approached a house
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.98,0:44:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,an elderly Mapuche woman came to the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.55,0:44:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,She was scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.42,0:44:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So straight away I greeted her in Mapudungún.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.93,0:44:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,She invited us inside and spoke with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.47,0:44:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.47,0:44:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I had spoken about Jehovah in my mother tongue.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.81,0:44:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,On our way back, I was deep in thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.44,0:45:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,praying to Jehovah\Nabout how to help the Mapuche people.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.28,0:45:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Many years passed
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.28,0:45:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,before I saw an answer to my prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.72,0:45:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Then one day after the meeting, I received
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.39,0:45:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,an invitation to be a speaker at the first assembly
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.69,0:45:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to include talks in Mapudungún.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.67,0:45:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But I didn’t want to accept the assignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.90,0:45:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt worthless because\Nof all the discrimination I had endured.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.47,0:45:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.47,0:45:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I prayed again and again to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.11,0:45:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and began to meditate a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.92,0:45:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah was now giving me\Nan answer to my prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.05,0:45:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He sees our true value.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.45,0:46:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so happy, so very happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.52,0:46:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I understood that Jehovah loved me
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.52,0:46:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and cared for me\Nand that he would continue to help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.62,0:46:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In just a few years, not one,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.16,0:46:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but several Mapudungún congregations were formed.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.10,0:46:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And now my wife and I,\Nas well as our two children,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.27,0:46:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,serve in Mapudungún-language congregations.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.90,0:46:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve been assisting with Mapudungún translation
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.24,0:46:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,for more than seven years now.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.04,0:46:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,When I tell the brothers and sisters\Nwho work with me at the translation office
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.71,0:46:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,about my childhood dream of becoming a teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.75,0:46:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,they tell me, “You’re our teacher now.”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.56,0:46:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to say to my brothers\Nand sisters around the world:
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.96,0:46:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“Don’t put yourselves down.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.96,0:46:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“You are precious; you are precious to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.23,0:46:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He will always help you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.26,0:47:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It took courage for Juan\Nto overcome his fear of discrimination.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.26,0:47:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In our lives as Christians,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.76,0:47:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,we can imitate Juan’s example\Nof courage in many different ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.37,0:47:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When we do,\Nlet’s remember the words of Joshua 1:9:
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.37,0:47:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“Have I not commanded you?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.78,0:47:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“Be courageous and strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.31,0:47:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not be struck with terror or fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.22,0:47:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,for Jehovah your God\Nis with you wherever you go.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.99,0:47:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,With that scripture in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.99,0:47:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,please enjoy the music video\Nfor this month entitled
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.86,0:48:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Be Courageous and Strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.86,0:48:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s dark outside.\NTo start the day,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.07,0:48:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,She humbly starts to pray\NFor her kids at school
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.54,0:48:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And the brotherhood:\N“Father, help us be faithful.”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.12,0:48:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,When things make it hard to cope,\NShe never thinks of losing hope,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.59,0:48:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Never stops being kind.\NAnd that song—it’s always on her mind:
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.57,0:48:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I will make you strong.\NDo not be afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.78,0:49:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I will be with you.\NI will be your aid.’
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.29,0:49:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Be courageous and strong.\NIt’s her favorite song.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.00,0:49:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And “he will make you firm,\NAnd he will make you strong.”
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.18,0:49:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Time to get on her feet—\NTry to make ends meet—
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.45,0:49:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Never sure what to expect.\NHer true friends out there
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.56,0:49:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Really show her they care,\NSo she never needs to fret.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.67,0:50:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,She’ll soar on wings\NTo rise up high,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.34,0:50:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Like eagles in the sky.\NAll the roles she plays—
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.21,0:50:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So little time each day—\NAnd in her heart, she starts to pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.29,0:50:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Aching feet and tired hands—\NShe tries the very best she can.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.90,0:50:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But there’s strength she can find\NIn that song that’s always on her mind:
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.24,0:51:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I will make you strong.\NDo not be afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.48,0:51:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I will be with you.\NI will be your aid.’
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.66,0:51:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Be courageous and strong.\NIt’s her favorite song.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.13,0:51:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And “he will make you firm,\NAnd he will make you strong.”
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.31,0:51:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And “he will make you firm,\NAnd he will make you strong.”
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.83,0:51:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve seen many examples of modesty
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.40,0:51:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,on the program this month.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.93,0:52:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,First, the McConnell sisters helped us appreciate
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.77,0:52:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that true family happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.77,0:52:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,is only possible when we\Nfollow Jehovah’s principles.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.74,0:52:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Modest parents know their limitations
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.68,0:52:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and will rely on Jehovah’s guidance.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.38,0:52:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,After the talk,\Nwe saw how a young brother’s modesty
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.15,0:52:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,protected him from sinning against Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.62,0:52:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we saw examples\Nof organizational achievements,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.33,0:52:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,all of which require modesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.20,0:52:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw this not only\Nin the Faith in Action Museum at Warwick
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.53,0:52:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,but also with the satellite provision
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.90,0:52:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for JW Broadcasting®
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.00,0:52:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in sub-Saharan Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.14,0:52:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And we need to be careful not to confuse
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.64,0:52:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,our imperfect view of ourselves with modesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.61,0:52:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, we should do all we can\Nto support Jehovah’s work.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.82,0:52:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we do,\NJehovah will support us,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.46,0:52:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,as this month’s music video highlighted.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.93,0:53:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And later this month,\Nyou’ll find an exciting report
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.50,0:53:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,on Video on Demand.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.66,0:53:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s about the work of the Publishing Committee\Nof the Governing Body.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.47,0:53:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So tune in again for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.27,0:53:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,To conclude,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.27,0:53:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s visit our brothers\Nand sisters in Tasmania, Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.25,0:53:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Tasmania is Australia’s smallest state
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.55,0:53:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and is an island located about 240 kilometers,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.82,0:53:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,or 150 miles, south of the mainland.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.32,0:53:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite its small land mass,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.76,0:53:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s known for its very diverse landscape
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.80,0:53:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,featuring beautiful yet rugged mountain,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.93,0:53:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,lake, and coastal landscapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.00,0:53:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The central plateau\Nis a prominent feature of Tasmania,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.34,0:53:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,thanks to its more than 4,000 lakes
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.44,0:53:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of glacial origin.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.71,0:53:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This island is home to close to 1,800 publishers
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.75,0:53:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in 22 congregations.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.75,0:54:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the Huonville Congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.49,0:54:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They care for Australia’s southernmost territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.36,0:54:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Although their territory is vast
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.93,0:54:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and many of the publishers\Nare advanced in years,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.33,0:54:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the congregation is known\Nto assist neighboring congregations
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.34,0:54:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,with their territories.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.41,0:54:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In 2016,\Nthe Huonville Congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.08,0:54:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,was happy to see\Ntheir Kingdom Hall get renovated.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.65,0:54:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And when visiting brothers\Ncome to give a public talk in Huonville,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.95,0:54:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s not unusual that they get\Na box of local produce as a gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.49,0:54:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers and sisters\Nin the Huonville Congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.13,0:54:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,send us their warm Christian love,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.23,0:54:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and we love them very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.90,0:54:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Until next month,\Nthis is JW Broadcasting
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.94,0:55:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,from the World Headquarters\Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses.
